<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7361] VerifyError when private variable is used in synchronized block</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7361</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the following code, synchronizing on the &lt;b&gt;private&lt;/b&gt; final field map inside a closure causes a &lt;tt&gt;VerifyError&lt;/tt&gt;. Synchronizing on a protected or public field fixes the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;TaskManager {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Map&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; map = [1L:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;a&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,2L:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;b&apos;&lt;/span&gt;]
    void doh() {
        def list = [1L]
        list.each {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;synchronized&lt;/span&gt; (map) {
                map.remove(it)
            }
        }
    }
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; TaskManager().doh()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
